In Week 3, we worked as a team to clean and prepare the technical support dataset. Data cleaning is a crucial step 
because raw datasets may contain missing values, duplicate entries, or inconsistent formats.

Data Cleaning Process:

During the team work session, the following data cleaning steps were performed:
- Removing duplicate records
- Handling missing or null values
- Standardizing date and time formats
- Correcting inconsistent category names
- Verifying column data types

Data Transformation:

After cleaning the dataset, additional transformations were performed using Power Query. 
Calculated columns such as Resolution Time were created to measure how long it takes to resolve support tickets.

Team Collaboration:

The cleaning process was completed as a team effort where members worked together to review the dataset, 
identify issues, and apply appropriate data cleaning techniques.

Outcome:
After completing the cleaning process, the dataset was properly structured and ready for analysis in Power BI. 
The processed data will be used to create KPIs and dashboards to evaluate IT support team performance.
